                                                                  5053 1451
  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     5053 1451
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        5053 1451
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     5053 1451
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     5053 1451
          (2012) 2841.                                            5053 1451
                                                                  5053 1451
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           5053 1451
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         5053 1451
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR5053 1451
       expands from 0 to 2.806693E+2 eV. A total of               5053 1451
       2 l-values are used and 39 resonances. The resonance       5053 1451
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              5053 1451
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       5053 1451
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          5053 1451
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     5053 1451
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    5053 1451
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  5053 1451
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   5053 1451
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          5053 1451
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       5053 1451
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    5053 1451
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       5053 1451
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         5053 1451
       The s-wave average level spacing is 20.86 eV and           5053 1451
       the s-wave neutron strength is 7.643e-05 1e-4.             5053 1451
                                                                  5053 1451
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  5053 1451
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    5053 1451
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    5053 1451
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   5053 1451
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    5053 1451
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              5053 1451
